(In reply to Matthias Andree from comment #3)

[The rpi2 is busy currently and I' do not have access to a big-endian system for weeks/months. The experiments will not be tonight.]

I clearly messed up in not showing the compiler messages originally. I also omitted the forward declarations of the two routines --and those are important to the messages.

(Editing out escape sequences. . .)

../util/db_tuner.c:1115:12: warning: promoted type 'int' of K&R function parameter is not compatible with the parameter type 'db_indx_t' (aka 'unsigned short')
      declared in a previous prototype [-Wknr-promoted-parameter]
        db_indx_t indx;
                 ^
../util/db_tuner.c:127:51: note: previous declaration is here
static int item_space __P((DB *, PAGE *, db_indx_t));
                                                  ^
../util/db_tuner.c:1127:12: warning: promoted type 'int' of K&R function parameter is not compatible with the parameter type 'db_indx_t' (aka 'unsigned short')
      declared in a previous prototype [-Wknr-promoted-parameter]
        db_indx_t indx;
                  ^
../util/db_tuner.c:126:50: note: previous declaration is here
static int item_size __P((DB *, PAGE *, db_indx_t));

# grep item_space */*.[hc]
util/db_tuner.c:static int item_space __P((DB *, PAGE *, db_indx_t));
util/db_tuner.c:			onpd_sz += item_space(dbp, h, indx);
util/db_tuner.c:				onpd_sz += item_space(dbp, h, indx + O_INDX);
util/db_tuner.c:		sz += item_space(dbp, h, i);
util/db_tuner.c:item_space(dbp, h, indx)

# grep item_size */*.[hc]
util/db_tuner.c:static int item_size __P((DB *, PAGE *, db_indx_t));
util/db_tuner.c:			key_sz = item_size(dbp, h, indx);
util/db_tuner.c:				data_sz = item_size(dbp, h, indx + O_INDX);
util/db_tuner.c:			key_sz = item_size(dbp, h, indx);
util/db_tuner.c:		data_sz = item_size(dbp, h, indx + O_INDX);
util/db_tuner.c:		data_sz = item_size(dbp, h, indx);
util/db_tuner.c:item_size(dbp, h, indx)

I should have originally included the forward declarations that are function prototypes:

static int item_size __P((DB *, PAGE *, db_indx_t));
static int item_space __P((DB *, PAGE *, db_indx_t));

I'll note:

build_unix/db.h:#undef __P
build_unix/db.h:#define       __P(protos)     protos

Also the implementations are last, after the calling code.

So the forward declarations have modern function-prototype notation but the later routine implementations use old K&R notation.

And that is what the compiler complaints are actually about --not about the calls mismatching.

If I had done the work to include such source in the original submittal I'd have noticed the additional issue and that the calls were not really what the compiler complaints were about.

My apologies for my submittal screw-ups.
